# Cloudflare Pages redirects / rewrites
# Syntax: <from>  <to>  <status>
# Reference: https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/redirects/
#
# Order matters - Cloudflare matches the first rule. Static files (assets,
# /install, _shell.html, etc.) take precedence over these rules; this file
# only governs routes that don't match a real file.

# SPA fallback - any unmatched path serves the TanStack Start SPA shell
# with a 200 (URL stays as-is, React Router renders the matching route).
# This is the catch-all for /features, /showcases, /origin, /old-landing,
# /how-it-works, /docs/*, /manifesto, /brand, /releases/*, etc.
#
# Target is /index.html (a copy of _shell.html emitted by the build), NOT
# /_shell.html: Cloudflare Pages auto-redirects any *.html URL to its
# extensionless form (308), so a `/_shell.html` rewrite target gets bounced to
# /_shell and the /* rule re-matches -> infinite 308 loop. index.html is served
# as the directory index without that redirect, breaking the loop.
/*  /index.html  200
